markdownRemark.html: I'm struck by how both math books and handwriting books seem to come of age during the pontificate of Clement VII. Presumably this is just a coincidence. In any case, one has to feel for anyone who hoped that the disastrous papal jubilee of 1525 would be key to his publishing success.
